<h1 id="ms-js-miliseconds-conversion-utility">ms.js: miliseconds conversion utility</h1>
<pre class="highlight javascript"><code><span class="nx">ms</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'2 days'</span><span class="p">)</span>  <span class="c1">// 172800000</span>
<span class="nx">ms</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'1d'</span><span class="p">)</span>      <span class="c1">// 86400000</span>
<span class="nx">ms</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'10h'</span><span class="p">)</span>     <span class="c1">// 36000000</span>
<span class="nx">ms</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'2.5 hrs'</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="c1">// 9000000</span>
<span class="nx">ms</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'2h'</span><span class="p">)</span>      <span class="c1">// 7200000</span>
<span class="nx">ms</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'1m'</span><span class="p">)</span>      <span class="c1">// 60000</span>
<span class="nx">ms</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'5s'</span><span class="p">)</span>      <span class="c1">// 5000</span>
<span class="nx">ms</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'100'</span><span class="p">)</span>     <span class="c1">// 100</span>
</code></pre>
<pre class="highlight javascript"><code><span class="nx">ms</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">60000</span><span class="p">)</span>             <span class="c1">// "1m"</span>
<span class="nx">ms</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">2</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="mi">60000</span><span class="p">)</span>         <span class="c1">// "2m"</span>
<span class="nx">ms</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nx">ms</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'10 hours'</span><span class="p">))</span>    <span class="c1">// "10h"</span>
</code></pre>
<pre class="highlight javascript"><code><span class="nx">ms</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">60000</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="p">{</span> <span class="na">long</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="kc">true</span> <span class="p">})</span>             <span class="c1">// "1 minute"</span>
<span class="nx">ms</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">2</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="mi">60000</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="p">{</span> <span class="na">long</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="kc">true</span> <span class="p">})</span>         <span class="c1">// "2 minutes"</span>
<span class="nx">ms</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nx">ms</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'10 hours'</span><span class="p">),</span> <span class="p">{</span> <span class="na">long</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="kc">true</span> <span class="p">})</span>    <span class="c1">// "10 hours"</span>
</code></pre>

<ul>
<li>Node/Browser compatible. Published as <a href="https://www.npmjs.org/package/ms"><code class="prettyprint">ms</code></a> in <a href="http://nodejs.org/download">NPM</a>.</li>
<li>If a number is supplied to <code class="prettyprint">ms</code>, a string with a unit is returned.</li>
<li>If a string that contains the number is supplied, it returns it as
a number (e.g: it returns <code class="prettyprint">100</code> for <code class="prettyprint">&#39;100&#39;</code>).</li>
<li>If you pass a string with a number and a valid unit, the number of
equivalent ms is returned.</li>
</ul>

